text:
Ben is a very pro active problem solver who's fun to watch and root for (using an internal door to reinforce an external door is pretty clever). 
Cooper is a jerk, which is probably why no one wants to listen to him, but that doesn't mean he's not thinking or has a wrong take on the situation, making him an interesting foil for Ben. 
Tom is a gem.
Jenny seems pretty ride or die for Tom, choosing to go with him into the danger rather than sit by and have him go in alone. Though it lead to their doom when she got stuck, i can still respect the decision to follow.
Barbara, though mostly a do nothing, serves as an interesting trauma case as someone who keeps having to re confront the cruelty of the new world. from watching her brother die, to having every new person she meets say "what's wrong with her? oh, her brother's dead" to meeting him again, but as an undead.
the anti undead task force was was also fascinating to see. in every other zombie media you have every marshal authority overwhelmed by zombies and you then have people left on their own with no hope of rescue or aid, which would make Ben's plan of action more viable. But in this case you actually had an organized group of people combing the land for undead (mostly), which made cooper's plan of action more viable.
